cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

The paper proposes a vision-based technique for detecting power lines to facilitate self-driving UAVs and automatic obstacle avoidance. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of the proposed approach as a valuable component of self-driving UAVs, which suggests robotics (cs.RO) as another likely category. The LS-Net is a deep learning model, and the paper proposes a series of effective data augmentation techniques, which suggests artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) as likely categories. Finally, the paper deals with detecting power lines, which are a type of geometric object, and proposes a line segment detector, which suggests graphics (cs.GR) as a possible category.
